B.Zj=new A.a_(B.a0A,["PL OMAHA Practice","Board Reading","Pot Limit Calculation","Pot Limit Calculator","Donate","Game Info","OK","Language","made by SNO","This game helps you improve your board reading skills in Omaha Poker. Practice analyzing various hands and community cards to find the winner.","Practice calculating pot limit betting amounts in Omaha Poker. Develop your ability to quickly calculate accurate pot limit amounts in various situations.","Omaha Poker Board Reading Guide","Start Game","Next Game","Correct! +1 point\nCurrent score: ","Wrong!\nCorrect answer: ","Enter POT! amount","Submit","SB","BB","ALL-IN","FOLD","CALL","RAISE","POT!","Game Over","Final Score","High Score","Congratulations","New High Score","Winning Hand","Correct answer is","End Replay (Return to Current Round)","Community Cards","Remaining Time","sec","Player Count","Round","selected","correct","wrong","score","Review","Board Reading Guide","View Calculation","POT! Calculation","Current Pot","Call Amount","Calculation","POT! Betting","Answer","Apply Blinds","Custom Blinds","Use Random Blinds","Game has not started yet.","Pot Limit Guide","Maximum betting amount in Pot Limit Omaha:","1. Calculate current pot size","2. Calculate call amount","3. Maximum bet = Current pot + Call amount + Call amount","POT! = Current pot + Call amount x 2","Example:","\u2022 Current pot: 1000","\u2022 Call amount: 300","\u2022 POT! betting = 1000 + 300 x 2 = 1600","Thus, a player can bet up to 1600 maximum.","Manual Setting","Please enter a valid number.","Key Rules for PLO Dealers",u.A,u.x,u.h,u.m,u.a,"Important Notes for Hand Judging",u.I,u.G,u.M,u.n,u.r,"Common Confusing Situations",u.X,u.v,u.Y,u.F,u.y,"Hand Reading Skills",u.f,u.B,u.H,u.R,u.d,"How to Play This App",u.Z,u.P,u.K,u.D,u.C,u.W,u.q,"A simple calculator to quickly calculate pot limit amounts. Just enter the current pot and call amount to instantly get the maximum possible bet."],t.w)
